This is an excerpt from the Cherokee Supreme Court docket for the years 1823 to 1834. The Cherokee Supreme Court convened annually in New Echota beginning on the second Monday in October and lasting three weeks. This excerpt is from the Wednesday November 1, 1826 session of court, during which a case over the rights to a slave woman was heard. Entries from this Supreme Court docket cover items ch100-ch163.

body.value: Wednesday 1st Nov. November 1826 The court met according to adjournment Present their honors, John Martin , Jas. James Daniel , Jas. Brown & Walter S. Adair Sarah West vs. Jno. John Walker Sn. Senior & Katy five Killer Try rights for a negro woman Quaity & her two children. The Court decide that Mrs. West is entitled to the negro woman Quaity only.
